M||tx|---
M||titl|Use Lazy State Initialization
M||impa|md
M||impa|wasted computation on every render
M||tags|rc, hooks, useState, perf, initialization
M||tx|---
M|Use |tx|Pass a fn to `useState` for expensive initial values. w/o the fn form, the initializer runs on every render even though the value is only used once.
M|Use |**In|**
M|Use |tx|```tsx
M|Use |func|{ items: Item[] }) {
M|Use |tx|// buildSearchIndex() runs on EVERY render, even after initialization
M|Use |tx|const [searchIndex, setSearchIndex] = useState(buildSearchIndex(items))
M|Use |tx|const [query, setQuery] = useState('')
M|Use |tx|// When query changes, buildSearchIndex runs again unnecessarily
M|Use |tx|return <SearchResults index={searchIndex} query={query} />
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|fn UserProfile() {
M|Use |tx|// JSON.parse runs on every render
M|Use |tx|const [settings, setSettings] = useState(
M|Use |tx|JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('settings') \|\| '{}')
M|Use |tx|)
M|Use |tx|return <SettingsForm settings={settings} onChange={setSettings} />
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|```
M|Use |**Co|**
M|Use |tx|```tsx
M|Use |func|{ items: Item[] }) {
M|Use |tx|// buildSearchIndex() runs ONLY on initial render
M|Use |tx|const [searchIndex, setSearchIndex] = useState(() => buildSearchIndex(items))
M|Use |tx|const [query, setQuery] = useState('')
M|Use |tx|return <SearchResults index={searchIndex} query={query} />
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|fn UserProfile() {
M|Use |tx|// JSON.parse runs only on initial render
M|Use |tx|const [settings, setSettings] = useState(() => {
M|Use |tx|const stored = localStorage.getItem('settings')
M|Use |retu|{}
M|Use |tx|})
M|Use |tx|return <SettingsForm settings={settings} onChange={setSettings} />
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|```
M|Use |tx|Use lazy initialization when computing initial values from localStorage/sessionStorage, building data structures (indexes, maps), reading from the DOM, or performing heavy transformations.
M|Use |tx|For simple primitives (`useState(0)`), direct references (`useState(props.value)`), or cheap literals (`useState({})`), the fn form is unnecessary.